# Direct (top-level) Python dependencies. The lockfile `requirements.txt`
# is regenerated from this file via:
#
#     pip-compile --generate-hashes --strip-extras requirements.in
#
# `--generate-hashes` adds sha256 of every wheel/sdist on PyPI to the
# lockfile, so a future PyPI compromise that publishes a malicious
# package with the same VERSION (rare but happens) fails the
# `pip install --require-hashes` step in CI + Dockerfile.
#
# Pin patches conservatively (==) on security-critical libs to avoid
# implicit minor-version upgrades; use ~= on app-level deps where minor
# bumps are usually safe. Dependabot bumps both via the `pip` ecosystem
# in .github/dependabot.yml.
#
# Operator one-time setup:
#   pip install pip-tools
#   make lock-python   # regenerates requirements.txt with hashes

